The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Monday, April 18, 2005 

 French scribe held in Bangla

 Dhaka, April 17 (Reuters): Bangladesh police have detained a French freelance journalist and his Indian guide at the western Satkhira border with India, police said today.

 Arnaud Mondagaran was taken into custody on Friday for entering Bangladesh without valid travel documents, officials said. He identified himself as a French freelance journalist and film producer.

 ?We have arrested Frenchman Arnaud Mondagaran and his Indian assistant for suspicious movement,? inspector general of police Hadis Uddin said.

 Police said Arnaud would be sent to Dhaka for interrogation while the detained Indian, Mofizul Islam, was in police custody in Satkhira. 




